<div id="node-3323" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/DeploySpringAppsOnCloudFoundry" title="Video: Deploy Spring Applications on Cloud Foundry">Video: Deploy Spring Applications on Cloud Foundry</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Adam Fitzgerald on Mon, 2011-12-05 19:53        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p><a href="http://blog.springsource.org/author/ramnivasl/">Ramnivas Laddad</a> has created a new short video about how to <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OIj_IVcZKfM">deploy Spring applications to Cloud Foundry</a>. He takes a straightforward Spring web application that uses a single data source and ports it directly to Cloud Foundry without having to make any code modifications.  This demonstrates the incredible intelligence that Cloud Foundry has about Spring applications - why don't you try moving your Spring application up to Cloud Foundry?
</p>

<p style="text-align: center"><object width="560" height="349">
<param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/OIj_IVcZKfM?version=3&amp;hl=en_US" />
